    BIO

    Hi, I'm Shane Stewart. Passionate about technology and gaming! I have been an intern at UCSD Radlab, working with a team on video game development. I have also worked at NFAR, the National Foundation for Autism Research

    MY EXPERIENCE

    At UCSD RadLab, collaborated on a video game development project using the platform Unity. The game is called Equilibrium, and is a obstacle course type game. With the balance board attachment, this game will be used to measure a users balance 

    Working with the National Foundation for Autism Research. Software testing and studying to become an A+ Certified computer technician
